cs.CL, cs.SE, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper discusses sentiment analysis and opinion mining, which are natural language processing techniques. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper focuses on extracting software quality properties from software reviews. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses the challenges of mining software reviews, which involves retrieving and analyzing large amounts of text data. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for sentiment analysis. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the impact of software reviews on users and teams.
